## 📊 Where you'll see this error:

1. **Sentry Dashboard:** https://sentry.io/organizations/zenith-9l1/projects/javascript-nextjs/
2. **Browser Console:** `ReferenceError: myUndefinedFunction is not defined`
3. **Server logs:** If it happens during SSR

## 🛠️ Example of how to properly use Sentry instrumentation:

Based on your configuration guidance, here's how you could instrument this properly:

```javascript
import * as Sentry from '@sentry/nextjs';

function TestComponent() {
  const handleTestButtonClick = () => {
    // Create a transaction/span to measure performance
    Sentry.startSpan(
      {
        op: "ui.click",
        name: "Test Undefined Function Call",
      },
      (span) => {
        span.setAttribute("test_type", "error_simulation");
        span.setAttribute("expected_outcome", "ReferenceError");

        try {
          myUndefinedFunction(); // This will throw an error
        } catch (error) {
          Sentry.captureException(error);
          throw error; // Re-throw to maintain normal error flow
        }
      },
    );
  };

  return (
    <button type="button" onClick={handleTestButtonClick}>
      Test Sentry Error Tracking
    </button>
  );
}
```

Your Sentry setup is now ready to catch and track all errors in production! 🎯

